This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial appearance changes caused by makeup and proposes a method for makeup-invariant face verification. The use of deep learning networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves image synthesis, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the use of adversarial networks for preserving identity information could suggest that it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with face verification, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
